{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:proverbs.30",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 30 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:1",
      "text": "The words of Agur the son of Jakeh, even the prophecy: the man spake unto Ithiel, even unto Ithiel and Ucal,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:2",
      "text": "Surely I am more brutish than any man, and have not the understanding of a man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:3",
      "text": "I neither learned wisdom, nor have the knowledge of the holy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:4",
      "text": "Who hath ascended up into heaven, or descended? who hath gathered the wind in his fists? who hath bound the waters in a garment? who hath established all the ends of the earth? what is his name, and what is his son’s name, if thou canst tell?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:5",
      "text": "Every word of God is pure: he is a shield unto them that put their trust in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:6",
      "text": "Add thou not unto his words, lest he reprove thee, and thou be found a liar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:7",
      "text": "Two things have I required of thee; deny me them not before I die:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:8",
      "text": "Remove far from me vanity and lies: give me neither poverty nor riches; feed me with food convenient for me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:9",
      "text": "Lest I be full, and deny thee, and say, Who is the Lord? or lest I be poor, and steal, and take the name of my God in vain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:10",
      "text": "Accuse not a servant unto his master, lest he curse thee, and thou be found guilty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:11",
      "text": "There is a generation that curseth their father, and doth not bless their mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:12",
      "text": "There is a generation that are pure in their own eyes, and yet is not washed from their filthiness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:13",
      "text": "There is a generation, O how lofty are their eyes! and their eyelids are lifted up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:14",
      "text": "There is a generation, whose teeth are as swords, and their jaw teeth as knives, to devour the poor from off the earth, and the needy from among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:15",
      "text": "The horseleach hath two daughters, crying, Give, give. There are three things that are never satisfied, yea, four things say not, It is enough:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:16",
      "text": "The grave; and the barren womb; the earth that is not filled with water; and the fire that saith not, It is enough.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:17",
      "text": "The eye that mocketh at his father, and despiseth to obey his mother, the ravens of the valley shall pick it out, and the young eagles shall eat it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:18",
      "text": "There be three things which are too wonderful for me, yea, four which I know not:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:19",
      "text": "The way of an eagle in the air; the way of a serpent upon a rock; the way of a ship in the midst of the sea; and the way of a man with a maid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:20",
      "text": "Such is the way of an adulterous woman; she eateth, and wipeth her mouth, and saith, I have done no wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:21",
      "text": "For three things the earth is disquieted, and for four which it cannot bear:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:22",
      "text": "For a servant when he reigneth; and a fool when he is filled with meat;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:23",
      "text": "For an odious woman when she is married; and an handmaid that is heir to her mistress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:24",
      "text": "There be four things which are little upon the earth, but they are exceeding wise:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:25",
      "text": "The ants are a people not strong, yet they prepare their meat in the summer;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:26",
      "text": "The conies are but a feeble folk, yet make they their houses in the rocks;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:27",
      "text": "The locusts have no king, yet go they forth all of them by bands;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:28",
      "text": "The spider taketh hold with her hands, and is in kings’ palaces.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:29",
      "text": "There be three things which go well, yea, four are comely in going:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:30",
      "text": "A lion which is strongest among beasts, and turneth not away for any;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:31",
      "text": "A greyhound; an he goat also; and a king, against whom there is no rising up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:32",
      "text": "If thou hast done foolishly in lifting up thyself, or if thou hast thought evil, lay thine hand upon thy mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.30.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:33",
      "text": "Surely the churning of milk bringeth forth butter, and the wringing of the nose bringeth forth blood: so the forcing of wrath bringeth forth strife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
